### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. UPDATE SUBSCRIPTION
###    Only send fields you want to change. subscriptionId is always required.
###    Replace SUB_REPLACE_ME with an ID returned from a subscribe call.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3a. Change amount and debit day
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/update
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "{{mandateId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAmount": "75.00",
  "debitDay": "20",
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "4" },
    { "name": "skipFactor", "value": "1" },
    { "name": "daysToDebitDayNotice", "value": "2,5" }
  ]
}

###

### 3b. Subscription not found — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/update
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "00000000-2655-4b0e-ad58-ec670ee99f50",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAmount": "75.00"
}


